#!hexa strict
// qmirror/chemistry_vqe/module/chemistry_vqe_cmt_uccsd_lih_4e5o_rfc037.hexa
//
// RFC 037 (farr_pauli_expectation_batch) migration of the LiH 4e/5o
// (8-qubit) chemistry_vqe module — HYBRID migration: keeps the existing
// hexa-side UCCSD ansatz loop (RFC 038 ansatz_pack currently returns -1
// on the running hexa runtime, so the ansatz leg is unchanged) while
// collapsing the Hamiltonian expectation hot loop (276 boxed-Val calls
// to `farr_pauli_expectation`) into ONE `farr_pauli_expectation_batch`
// C call followed by an N=276 packed-double scan via `farr_get`.
//
// Source module: `chemistry_vqe_cmt_uccsd_lih_4e5o.hexa` (legacy, kept
// untouched so we can A/B compare). All vendored data tables are
// imported from that module via the canonical `cv_uccsd_lih4e5o_cache()`
// builder + the public `cv_uccsd_lih4e5o_energy_h` reference.
//
// Migration plan (per RFC 037 §3.2):
//   1. Cache build: pack the 4 Hamiltonian mask arrays (`ham_flip`,
//      `ham_z`, `ham_y`, `ham_cy`) into 4 farr_int handles AND allocate
//      a reusable `ham_exp_buf` (farr_zeros(n_ham)).
//   2. Per-eval: one `farr_pauli_expectation_batch` call replaces the
//      276-iter hexa-side `farr_pauli_expectation` loop. Sum
//      `coef[k] * out[k]` over k=0..275 (still hexa-side, but only N
//      adds — no per-term kernel boxing).
//   3. Sentinel comparison harness: assert `|E_rfc037 - E_legacy| < 1e-12`
//      at 4 random theta points (incl. the all-zero |HF> energy).
//   4. Run NM (maxiter=200) with the migrated energy fn; record wall.
//
// @sentinel(__QMIRROR_BATCH_MIGRATION_LIH_4E5O__ <PASS|FAIL>)

// ─── Vendored data (mirror the legacy module verbatim) ──────────────────
//
// Same numbers as chemistry_vqe_cmt_uccsd_lih_4e5o.hexa. Re-declared here
// so this module is self-contained and runnable as a standalone hexa
// entrypoint without import-resolution dependencies (hexa's package
// import semantics in v0.1.0-dispatch are not yet stable for this
// usage pattern in qmirror).

